20a%20hard%20industry%20to%20get%20a%20job%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20rich%20parents%20or%20people%20that%20come%20from%20the%20industry%20to%20refer%20you%2C%20it's%20very%20hard%20for%20you%20to%20find%20an%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20come%20from%20the%20industry.%20I%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20career%20working%20at%20startups%20and%20had%20to%20brute-force%20my%20way%20to%20starting%20Wischoff%20Ventures%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20path%20into%20venture%20capital%20has%20colored%20my%20approach%20toward%20recruiting.%20I%20wanted%20to%20find%20hires%20like%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20might%20not%20have%20gone%20to%20Stanford%20or%20had%20some%20flashy%20names%20on%20their%20CVs%20but%20are%20willing%20to%20outwork%20any%20of%20those%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22342a1dae-a9ed-4ec9-aabb-26075a697992%5C%22%3EScreening%20through%20500%20applications%20to%20find%20the%20perfect%20hire%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20recruiting%20for%20my%20fund's%20first%20full-time%20hire%20earlier%20this%20year.%20I%20posted%20the%20position%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20X%20and%20got%20over%20500%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20seemed%20a%20lot%2C%20it%20wasn't%20difficult%20to%20filter%20down%20the%20numbers.%20For%20one%2C%2030%25%20of%20the%20applications%20were%20rejected%20because%20I%20needed%20someone%20based%20in%20San%20Francisco%20or%20New%20York.%20Those%20applicants%20were%20either%20not%20living%20there%20or%20didn't%20intend%20to%20move%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2030%25%20of%20the%20applications%20mainly%20came%20from%20people%20working%20in%20investment%20banking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20those%20candidates%20did%20have%20a%20deep%20background%20in%20finance%2C%20they%20weren't%20quite%20what%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%20Understanding%20ventures%2C%20especially%20early-stage%20ones%2C%20is%20very%20different%20from%20what%20they%20did%20in%20banking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2020%25%20of%