%22CEO%20of%20aerospace%20company%20cited%20in%20SpaceX's%20new%20lawsuit%20is%20siding%20with%20Elon%20Musk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221963%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jim%20Cantrell%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Phantom%20Space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67100cb53f2165d716e2391b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJim%20Cantrell%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Phantom%20Space%3Cp%3EJim%20Cantrell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESpaceX%20compared%20itself%20to%20another%20space%20company%20in%20its%20lawsuit%20against%20a%20California%20agency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPhantom%20Space%20CEO%20Jim%20Cantrell%2C%20a%20longtime%20colleague%20of%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20supports%20SpaceX.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E'It's%20very%20un-American%2C%20it's%20very%20anti-competitive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJim%20Cantrell%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Phantom%20Space%2C%20said%20he%20sides%20with%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-for-elon-musk-spacex-workplace-culture-twitter-jim-cantrell-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elongtime%20colleague%3C%2Fa%3E%20Elon%20Musk%20in%20SpaceX's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-free-speech-lawsuit-california-coastal-commission-spacex-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%2C%20telling%20Business%20Insider%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20surprised%20at%20how%20blatantly%20political%26quot%3B%20the%20commission%20had%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20is%20suing%20the%20commission%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%20overreach%2C%26quot%3B%20after%20members%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-launches-california-coastal-commission-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublicly%20criticized%20his%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20meeting%20and%20later%20rejected%20more%20frequent%20SpaceX%20launches%20off%20the%20California%20coastline%20at%20Vandenberg%20Space%20Force%20Base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20was%20seeking%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20launches%20each%20year%20from%2036%20to%2050.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20written%20decision%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20as%20a%20private%20company%2C%20SpaceX%20is%20not%20exempt%20from%20obtaining%20a%20permit%2C%20even%20though%20it%20works%20closely%20with%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20lawsuit%2C%20SpaceX%20accuses%20the%20commission%20of%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20biases%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20another%20commercial%20space%20operator%20similarly%20conducting%20a%20mix%20of%20commercial%20and%20federal%20work%20was%20recently%20approved%20for%2060%20launches%20out%20of%20Vandenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECantrell%2C%20a%20member%20of%20SpaceX's%20founding%20team%20and%20employee%20number%20four%20at%20the%20company%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20SpaceX%20is%20referencing%20Phantom%20Space%20in%20its%20suit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he's%20firmly%20on%20Musk's%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20who%20are%20representing%20government%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20state%20government%2C%20federal%20government%20%E2%80%94%20really%20shouldn't%20be%20basing%20their%20decisions%20on%20who%20you%20support%20for%20president%20or%20anybody%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Cantrell%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Finding%20of%20No%20Significant%20Impact%20(FONSI)%20document%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20signed%20by%20a%20United%20States%20Space%20Force%20executive%20in%20June%202024%20showed%20Phantom%20was%20given%20the%20all%20clear%20for%2048%20flights%20annually%20at%20Vandenberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECantrell%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20got%20approval%20for%2012%20launches%20at%20a%20separate%20Space%20Launch%20Complex%20at%20the%20base.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fdata_research%2Fcommercial_space_data%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20FAA%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20two%20operators%20have%20launched%20at%20Vandenberg%20this%20year%3A%20SpaceX%20and%20Firefly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20un-American%2C%20it's%20very%20anti-competitive%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20like%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Cantrell%20said%20of%20what%20he%20believes%20is%20commission%20bias.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I'm%20aligned%20with%20Elon%20on%20this%2C%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20having%20the%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%20retaliate%20against%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECantrell%20told%20BI%20he%2C%20unlike%20Musk%2C%20maintains%20political%20neutrality.%20Phantom%20uses%20smaller%20vehicles%20than%20SpaceX%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20a%20smaller%20environmental%20impact%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20very%2C%20very%20succinctly%20refuse%20to%20endorse%20politicians%2C%26quot%3B%20Cantrell%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20either%20going%20to%20piss%20off%20half%20the%20world%20and%20make%20the%20other%20half%20happy%20or%20piss%20off%20nobody.%20So%20I%20try%20to%20stay%20neutral.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20commission%20alleges%20the%20group%2C%20which%20regulates%20the%20use%20of%20land%20and%20water%20in%20California's%20coastal%20zone%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20engaged%20in%20naked%20political%20discrimination%26quot%3B%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20First%20and%2014th%20Amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20rocket%20company%20says%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20that%20the%20commission%20was%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bunlawfully%20regulate%20space%20launch%20programs%26quot%3B%20at%20Vandenberg%20military%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Vandenberg%20spokesman%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20ongoing%20litigation%20and%20said%20the%20base%20is%20working%20with%20state%20and%20federal%20agencies%20to%20%26quot%3Bensure%20safe%20and%20effective%20launch%20operations%20conducted%20under%20the%20existing%2036-launch%20agreement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20told%20BI%20Musk's%20complaint%20could%20be%20successful%20if%20the%20billionaire%20CEO%20can%20prove%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20facts%20are%20as%20alleged%2C%20and%20if%20Musk%20can%20prove%20that%20the%20decision%20would%20have%20been%20different%20had%20his%20politics%20been%20different%20or%20had%20he%20been%20apolitical%2C%20then%20the%20First%20Amendment%20arguments%20should%20likely%20prevail%2C%26quot%3B%20Eugene%20Volokh%2C%20a%20First%20Amendment%20scholar%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20%26quot%3Bhas%20to%20show%20that%20his%20politics%20were%20a%20substantial%20factor%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20commission's%20decision%2C%20said%20Volokh%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20UCLA%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hoover%20Institution%20at%20Stanford%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%2C%20if%20he%20does%20that%2C%20the%20commission%20would%20have%20to%20prove%20that%20it%20would%20have%20reached%20the%20same%20result%20regardless%20of%20his%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Volokh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Driesen%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Syracuse%20University%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3BPoliticians%20have%20a%20First%20Amendment%20right%20to%20criticize%20Musk%2C%20so%20accusing%20him%20of%20spreading%20falsehoods%20is%20protected%20political%20speech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Driesen%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20Musk%20could%20show%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20deny%20his%20application%20was%20punishment%20for%20his%20falsehoods%2C%20that%20might%20make%20out%20a%20First%20Amendment%20violation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDriesen%20pointed%20out%20that%20SpaceX's%20lawsuit%20emphasizes%20an%20administrati