20question%20for%20our%20columnist%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%226d5ba97ad0b8803692c5d48655c5380b%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDear%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20am%20wealthy%2C%20and%20my%20friends%20always%20hint%20about%20their%20money%20problems.%20When%20I%20travel%2C%20I%20don't%20tell%20them%2C%20but%20if%20they%20know%2C%20they%20resent%20it.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20deal%20with%20people%20who%20have%20no%20budget%20or%20plan%20for%20their%20money.%20I%20inherited%20money%20and%20invested%20it.%20I%20also%20worked%20and%20invested.%20Why%20can't%20they%20do%20the%20same%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20am%20not%20a%20bank.%20I%20donate%20to%20nonprofits%20for%20worthy%20causes.%20I%20am%20generous.%20But%20dealing%20with%20friends%20is%20difficult.%20And%20loaning%20money%20is%20losing%20the%20friendship.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do.%20Please%20tell%20me%20ways%20to%20say%20NO.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Friend%20With%20Money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Friend%20With%20Money%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20off%20I%20want%20to%20thank%20you%20for%20writing%20in.%20Knowing%20the%20general%20response%20to%20your%20predicament%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20collective%20groan%20%E2%80%94%20but%20choosing%20to%20share%20your%20experience%20anyway%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20brave%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20thinking%20about%20your%20letter%20before%20I%20sat%20down%20to%20respond.%20Maybe%20because%20it%20feels%20like%20a%20matter%20of%20taking%20sides%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20on%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20the%20poor%20friend%20passively%20trying%20to%20redirect%20my%20friend%20groups'%20vacation%20plans%20to%20a%20local%20winery%20when%20everyone%20else%20was%20getting%20excited%20about%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20the%20friend%20with%20money%20pretending%20not%20to%20notice%20a%20pal's%20insinuation%20that%20because%20I%20make%20more%20money%20than%20they%20do%2C%20I%20should%20pick%20up%20the%20tab.%20To%20clarify%2C%20both%20situations%20were%20awkward%20and%20unpleasant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20the%20poor%20friend%2C%20I%20couldn't%20sleep%20at%20night%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20tell%20my%20richer%20friends%20that%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20our%20annual%20girls'%20trip%20without%20feeling%20embarrassed%20and%20ashamed.%20As%20the%20friend%20with%20money%2C%20I%20couldn't%20sleep%20at%20night%20because%20I%20was%20worried%20my%20boundaries%20would%20end%20friendships%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20lose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHolding%20your%20boundaries%20is%20important%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20where%20I%20want%20to%20start%20%E2%80%94%20you%20made%20a%20few%20assumptions%20worth%20interrogating%20that%20I%20plan%20to%20tackle%20later%2C%20but%20ultimately%2C%20this%20situation%20comes%20down%20to%20your%20boundaries.%20You%20don't%20think%20it%20is%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20give%20or%20loan%20your%20friends%20cash.%20Therefore%2C%20you%20shouldn't.%20Your%20friends%20need%20to%20respect%20that%20boundary%20even%20if%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20logical%20or%20compassionate%20to%20them%2C%20and%20true%20friends%20will%20have%20this%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20holding%20any%20line%20can%20be%20tough%2C%20even%20when%20you%20know%20it's%20the%20smart%20thing%20to%20do.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20can%20know%20that%20loaning%20your%20friend%20money%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20lose%20that%20friend%2C%20but%20when%20they%20make%20an%20emotional%20appeal%2C%20staying%20true%20to%20that%20principle%20by%20looking%20them%20dead%20in%20the%20eye%20and%20saying%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20can%20be%20difficult.%20But%20there%20is%20value%20in%20sticking%20to%20your%20principles%20and%20holding%20your%20boundaries%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20losing%20friends.%20A%20boundary%20is%20a%20commitment%20you've%20made%20to%20yourself%2C%20which%20means%20by%20breaking%20that%20commitment%2C%20you're%20betraying%20yourself%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20breaking%20your%20self-trust.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20there%20you%20have%20it%3A%20my%20permission%20to%20ignore%20your%20friends'%20hints%20that%20you%20need%20to%20contribute%20financially%20to%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETry%20a%20little%20empathy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20let's%20talk%20about%20that%20word%20%26quot%3Bhinting.%26quot%3B%20A%20hint%20is%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20an%20indirect%20suggestion.%20Since%20you%20used%20this%20word%20to%20describe%20the%20way%20your%20friends%20ask%20you%20for%20money%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20you're%20interpreting%20something%20your%20friends%20have%20said%20as%20a%20request%20they've%20never%20actually%20made.%20I%20would%20encourage%20you%20to%20ask%20yourself%20if%20your%20interpretation%20of%20their%20motives%20could%20be%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20noticed%20you%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20travel%2C%20I%20don't%20tell%20them%2C%20but%20if%20they%20know%2C%20they%20resent%20it.%26quot%3B%20I%20find%20myself%20wondering%20what%20that%20resentment%20looks%20like.%20Are%20they%20making%20angry%20accusations%20that%20you%20ought%20to%20have%20brought%20them%20along%20for%20the%20ride%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20good-natured%20ribbing%20with%20a%20side%20of%20passive%20aggression%3F%20Or%20maybe%20it's%20more%20straightforward%20than%20that%2C%20and%20they%20simply%20respond%20to%20the%20news%20of%20your%20travels%20with%20a%20grumbled%20%26quot%3Bmust%20be%20nice%26quot%3B%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20first%20scenario%20is%20true%2C%20to%20be%20perfectly%20frank%2C%20your%20friends%20aren't%20worth%20keeping.%20But%20if%20one%20of%20the%20latter%20two%20options%20more%20closely%20resembles%20your%20situation%2C%20I%20think%20you%20should%20try%20a%20little%20empathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20likes%20snide%20digs%20and%20bitter%20asides%2C%20but%20your%20perspective%20on%20your%20friends'%20financial%20straits%20tells%20me%20that%20you're%20harboring%20a%20lot%20of%20resentment%20of%20your%20own.%20You%20were%20literally%20born%20into%20money%2C%20and%20since%20then%2C%20it%20sounds%20like%20you've%20made%20several%20smart%20financial%20moves%20that%20have%20increased%20your%20wealth.%20You%20should%20never%20feel%20like%20you%20have%20to%20apologize%20for%20either%20of%20those%20things%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20get%20to%20judge%20your%20friends%20for%20not%20achieving%20your%20level%20of%20financial%20success%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20can't%20they%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20I%20did%3F%26quot%3B%20try%20asking%20yourself%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20would%20it%20feel%20if%20I%20had%20financial%20struggles%20to%20the%20point%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20vacation%20and%20then%20I%20saw%20photos%20of%20my%20rich%20friend%20jet-setting%20across%20the%20globe%3F%26quot%3B%20If%20you're%20honest%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20probably%20something%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20a%20curled%20lip%20and%20an%20envious%20%26quot%3Bmust%20be%20nice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20people%20are%20your%20friends.%20You%20care%20about%20them%20deeply%20to%20the%20point%20of%20stressing%20over%20how%20the%20wrong%20move%20might%20cost%20you%20the%20relationship.%20So%2C%20if%20they%20need%20to%20roll%20their%20eyes%20after%20you%20mention%20your%20vacation%20to%20Maui%20and%20they%20want%20to%20mutter%20something%20