0to%20go%20public%2C%20Cisco%20offered%20to%20acquire%20the%20company%20for%20%243.7%20billion.%20As%20the%20founder%20and%20chairman%2C%20Bansal%20stood%20to%20gain%20significantly%20either%20way%2C%20but%20only%20one%20option%20ensured%20a%20substantial%20financial%20outcome%20for%20many%20of%20his%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20accepting%20Cisco's%20offer%2C%20approximately%20400%20AppDynamics%20employees%20saw%20the%20value%20of%20their%20shares%20soar%20to%20at%20least%20%241%20million%20each%2C%20according%20to%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Bansal.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20dozens%20of%20employees%20with%20%245%20million-plus%20outcomes.%20These%20are%20life-changing%20outcomes%2C%26quot%3B%20Bansal%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F09%2F30%2Fappdynamics-founder-why-i-regret-selling-my-startup-for-billions.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNBC%20Make%20It%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBansal's%20decision%20to%20sell%20was%20influenced%20by%20several%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20compatibility%20of%20AppDynamics'%20software%20products%20with%20Cisco's%20portfolio%20and%20the%20impact%20the%20sale%20would%20have%20on%20the%20company's%20nearly%201%2C200%20employees%2C%20both%20financially%20and%20culturally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20weighed%20Cisco's%20valuation%20of%20AppDynamics%20against%20his%20post-IPO%20projections%2C%20estimating%20that%20achieving%20a%20%243.7%20billion%20market%20cap%20would%20have%20required%20%26quot%3Bthree%20to%20four%20years%20of%20great%20execution%2C%26quot%3B%20along%20with%20the%20associated%20risks.%20By%20selling%2C%20he%20believed%20he%20minimized%20that%20risk%20for%20his%20employees%20and%20created%20significant%20financial%20benefits%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Mr%20Bansal%20later%20regretted%20the%20decision%2C%20feeling%20he%20could%20have%20continued%20to%20grow%20AppDynamics%20and%20experienced%20a%20sense%20of%20aimless